            <p>
<lb corresp="#a1"/><num value="24">20-4</num><w>kṣutsa</w><seg type="monogram">śṭhe</seg><w>lānti</w><w>yakw<supplied>e</supplied></w><gap reason="lost"/>
<w><supplied>wsa</supplied><lb corresp="#a2"/>ṣeñca</w><w>sāṅk</w><w>prāśnikeṃ</w><w>aśari</w><w>jñānasome</w><w>nauṣuwetsa</w><w>śānta</w><w>keś</w><w>tesare</w><w>tutse</w><w>keś</w>
<lb corresp="#a3"/><w>alyi</w><w>yriṃ</w><num value="5">5</num>
<lb corresp="#a4"/><w>orotsana</w><w>awi</w><num value="7">7</num>
<lb corresp="#a5"/><gap reason="plain" quantity="2"/><w><supplied>yr</supplied>iṃ</w><num value="10">10</num><w><gap reason="plain" unit="part"/>eśe</w><w>aiyyāna</w><w>śānta</w><w>takāre</w><num value="18">10-8</num></p>
         </div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">In the year 24 of the king Śṭhe(?), (a year of) horse ///</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">The interrogators/investigators (of) the <hi>saṃgha</hi> [living in] ..., headed up by <hi>Jñānasome</hi> the <hi>Aśari</hi>, counted the number of sheep(/goats). (Here is) the count:</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Male new-born: 5</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Big ewes: 7</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a5"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... [new-born: 10]. There have been ... ovine livestocks: 18.</seg></seg></choice></p>
         </div>
         <div type="comments">
            <p><note corresp="#a1" type="philcomment"><hi>śṭhe</hi>: monogram of the king's name, abbreviation of <hi>śreṣṭhe</hi>, a loan from Skt. <hi>śreṣṭha-</hi>.</note><note corresp="#a5" type="philcomment"><hi>[e]śe</hi>: strangely, the first akṣara actually consists of an independent vowel sign <hi>a</hi> with a diacritic <hi>ai</hi> vocalism.</note></p>
         </div>
